  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Weigh the flour into a bowl, add the baking powder, spoon in the yoghurt and add a big pinch of salt. Mix together in the bowl until you have a shaggy dough, then tip out onto a lightly floured work surface and knead for just a few minutes until you have a smooth dough. Put back into the bowl, cover and leave for 10 mins for the dough to relax."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, cut the cucumber into quarters lengthways, then into 1cm slices. Chunk up the tomatoes into bite-sized pieces and halve and thinly slice the red onion. Tip everything into a bowl with the olives, then drizzle in 2 tbsp oil, half of the red wine vinegar and sprinkle in the oregano. Season and toss well"
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Spoon the tahini into a small bowl and add the remaining red wine vinegar. Season and add 3-4 tbsp cold water until you have a drizzleable sauce."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Come back to the flatbreads. Tip back onto a lightly floured work surface and divide the dough into four. Flour each piece and roll out to an 18cm circle."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get a large frying pan over a medium-high heat. Once hot, add one of the flatbreads to the pan and cook for 1-2 mins until risen, bubbly and puffy, then flip and repeat on the other side. Wrap in a clean tea towel while you cook the rest."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get another large frying pan over a medium-high heat. Cut the halloumi into 1cm-thick slices. Put into the pan without any oil and cook for 1-2 mins on each side until golden brown, then flip and repeat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Spread each of the flatbreads with some of the tahini sauce, pile in some of the salad, hot chips if using, halloumi and finally some chilli sauce, if you’re a spice head like us."
    }
  ],
